									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/annemendelson/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Screen-Shot-2024-09-13-at-9.19.58-AM-100x100.png" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Screen-Shot-2024-09-13-at-9.19.58-AM.png 2x" alt="Anne Mendelson" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/annemendelson/">Anne Mendelson</a></h6>
										Anne Mendelson is a culinary historian and freelance writer specializing in food-related subjects. Her most recent book is <em>Chow Chop Suey: Food and the Chinese American Journey</em> (Columbia, 2016).																			</div>
